a wedding service.

1383
01:45:33,207 --> 01:45:35,801
(Fiona) Poor girl. No, I mean it! Poor girl!

1384
01:45:35,887 --> 01:45:39,926
She's not my favourite person, but I think
what you did today was unforgivable.

1385
01:45:40,007 --> 01:45:42,316
I can't bear to think about it.

1386
01:45:43,327 --> 01:45:44,806
Poor Hen.

1387
01:45:44,887 --> 01:45:48,277
- (Tom) Though... Iet's face facts.
- I'm sorry... I'm sorry...

1388
01:45:48,367 --> 01:45:52,076
If you weren't sure you wanted
to marry her today of all days,...

1389
01:45:52,167 --> 01:45:55,239
..i.e., your wedding day,...

1390
01:45:55,327 --> 01:45:58,763
..then it must be the right decision,
mustn't it?

1391
01:45:59,487 --> 01:46:00,522
Quite right.

1392
01:46:00,607 --> 01:46:04,600
It was a lovely dress.
I'm sure she'll find it useful for parties.

1393
01:46:08,087 --> 01:46:11,159
- What did he say, Charles?
- Says he blames himself.

1394
01:46:11,247 --> 01:46:14,364
- (Tom) Oh... Absolutely not.
- (Matthew) No, you mustn't, David.

1395
01:46:14,447 --> 01:46:16,438
They all blame you too.

1396
01:46:17,687 --> 01:46:21,282
- (doorbell)
- No, no. If there's music to be faced,...

1397
